Albert Fritz has reacted with shock to the gang rape of a 13-year-old girl in Nyanga last weekend. CAPE TOWN - Western Cape Social Development MEC Albert Fritz says he is 'sick and tired' of violence against women and children.He's reacted with shock to the gang rape of a 13-year-old girl in Nyanga last weekend.Fritz says his department will do what is needed to assist the police as well as the survivor. I m just sick and tired, sick and tired of continuous sexual violence being perpetrated by men within our society. Seven men between the ages of 18 and 20 are appearing in court on Friday in connection with the attack.Police are also hunting an eighth suspect.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)